column5: Leaving tonight for the Seuly out of Ear Falls. Any reports?Thanks much!

Hi Guys - the walleye are running too big to eat; you'll get tired of throwing the big ones back. Pike and musky are starting to attack early this year, fair number of smaller fish cut off near the boat. More and larger smallmouth caught nearer Ear Falls than any other year. Grouse numbers are OK but still on the rise after last year's very poor year.
